- Slope: $m = \frac{2}{3}$

- $y$-intercept: $b = -1$, so the line passes through $(0, -1)$

From $(0, -1)$, rise $2$ and run $3$ to reach $(3, 1)$.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.55]
 (-4,-4) grid (5,3);
 (-4.5,0) – (5.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-4.5) – (0,3.5) node[above] {$y$};

 in {-4,...,-1,1,2,...,5} {
 at (,-0.1) {$\x$};
 }
 in {-4,...,-1,1,2,3} {
 at (-0.1,) {$\y$};
 }

 (-3.5,-3.33) – (5,2.33);

 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,-1) circle (4pt) node[below left] {$(0,-1)$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (3,1) circle (4pt) node[above right] {$(3,1)$};

 (0,-1) – (3,-1);
 (3,-1) – (3,1);

 at (1.5,-1.4) { run $3$};
 at (3.6,0) { rise $2$};
tikzpicture
center

